# Shopify Theme Styling Guidelines

## CSS Organization
The main stylesheet is located at [theme/src/styles.css](mdc:theme/src/styles.css)

## CSS Architecture
- Use BEM methodology for class naming
- Organize CSS by component/feature
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Follow mobile-first responsive design

## Class Naming Convention
```css
/* Block */
.product-card { }

/* Element */
.product-card__title { }
.product-card__price { }

/* Modifier */
.product-card--featured { }
.product-card--sale { }
```

## CSS Custom Properties
```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #000000;
  --color-secondary: #ffffff;
  --font-size-base: 16px;
  --spacing-unit: 8px;
}
```

## Responsive Design
```css
/* Mobile first approach */
.container {
  padding: var(--spacing-unit);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    padding: calc(var(--spacing-unit) * 2);
  }
}
```

## Shopify-Specific Classes
- `.shopify-section`: Section wrapper
- `.shopify-section-{{ section.id }}`: Section-specific styling
- `.shopify-block`: Block wrapper
- `.shopify-block-{{ block.id }}`: Block-specific styling

## Best Practices
- Avoid inline styles (use external CSS)
- Use semantic class names
- Keep specificity low
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts
- Optimize for performance
- Test across different devices
